beer.beer_description:
Grain: Pale, Munich, Oats, & Wheat
Hops: Melba, Amarillo, Cascade, Centennial, & Mosaic

Nectar of the Hops is a big and  juicy IPA but low on bitterness at 28 IBUs.  Late additions give you the beautiful sweat and fruity nectar of the hops.

The beer had a piney, passionfruit nose and a smooth, creamy mouthfeel from the addition of oats and wheat.  The hops give the beer beautiful tropical fruit flavours with hints of pineapple, mango and lychees. This IPA is extremely sessionable. 

Nectar of the Hoos is perfect beer for our warmer months.
